# Research Briefing (CRITIC thread)

**Goal:** Prove: for any 9 nonzero vectors in F_p^3 NOT lying on a common affine hyperplane, with multiplicities p-1, there exists a short zero-sum.

This is Case A of the eta(C_p^3) upper bound. Case B is fully solved (see seed).

The most promising approach: project to C_p^2 using eta(C_p^2) = 3p-2, extract partial zero-sums, combine them. This is standard in additive combinatorics.

Alternatively: reduce to Case B by studying K_0 (the sum-0 part of the kernel).

